  "title": "Population and Sampling",
  "body": " Population and Sampling  Population: Any collection of individual items or units which are the subject of investigation.   Sampling Method: The goal of sampling is to create a sample that is representative of the population it is being drawn from. The size of population is represented using the letter and the size of sample is represented using the letter The most basic sampling methods are:    Simple Random Sampling: Every member of the population, has an equal chance of being selected for the sample, .     Stratified Sampling: The population, is split into non-overlapping groups (strate), then simple random sampling is done on each group to form a sample, For example: split population of student in 'women' and 'men' group.     Systematic Sampling: Every individual from the population, is placed in the sample,      Convenience Sampling (Voluntary response sample): Easily obtained individuals from the population, are placed in the sample, .     "
